A vintage 1960s-style technical illustration showing a meticulously organized workspace from a bird's eye view. The scene depicts a large mahogany desk with neatly arranged modular compartments, each containing miniature dioramas of different work activities: a tiny filing cabinet, a small globe, connecting tubes linking compartments together, and miniature screens showing abstract graphs. The color palette uses muted teals, burnt oranges, and cream tones typical of mid-century design. Brass mechanical gears subtly connect the compartments beneath the surface, suggesting seamless integration. A single potted monstera plant sits in the corner. The overall composition suggests a perfectly orchestrated system where everything has its place and works in harmony, rendered in the style of vintage technical manuals with subtle halftone textures and clean geometric shapes.
